Net Profit (TTM/latest) (2025-09-17): 103.70M INR

Title   : Urban Company Share Price Live: Shares listing today, GMP signals bumper debut
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-17T04:03:02
Fetched : 2025-09-17T04:21:48.488660
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/stock-markets/urban-company-share-price-urban-company-ipo-listing-today-live-updates/article70059673.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Urban Company Stocks Today, Urban Company IPO listing & share price live updates: Shares of Urban Company Ltd debut on bourses today. The most oversubscribed Rs 1,900-cr IPO received 103.63 times subscription on the last day of bidding.
- Listing date and price: September 17. Expected to list at over 50% premium
- Issue size: Rs 472 crore through sale new shares, and Rs 1,428 crore from sale of stakes by existing investors.
- Price Band: Rs 98-103
- Anchor portion: Rs 854 crore
- Use of funds: The company plans to use funds raised through the fresh issuance for new technology development and cloud infrastructure, lease payments for its offices, marketing activities, and general corporate purposes.
Catch live updates on IPO, subscription, price band, share price, GMP, listing price and more
- September 17, 2025 09:43
Urban Company IPO, share price listing live: India’s Most Popular Big IPO of the Year Poised to Begin Trading - Bloomberg
Urban’s IPO has raised optimism its success will rub off on other Indian startups. A slew of companies — from eyewear retailer Lenskart Solutions Ltd. to e-commerce retailer Meesho Ltd. and Walmart Inc.-backed PhonePe are preparing to list their shares.
Urban’s offering saw strong participation from both institutional and retail investors. The deal included the sale of new and existing shares.
Thanks to India’s abundance of cheap labor, Urban allows users to book many types of service professionals — from hair dressers to fumigators and plumbers — at competitive prices and fast.
Bloomberg input
- September 17, 2025 09:41
Urban Company IPO, share price listing live: Most-sought IPO received over 100x subscription
The ₹1,900-crore initial public offering (IPO) of Urban Company Ltd, the app-based beauty and home services platform, drew an overwhelming response on the final day of bidding. The issue was subscribed 103.63 times, with NSE data showing bids for 1,106.44 crore shares against 10.67 crore shares available.
- September 17, 2025 09:36
Urban Company share price listing live today: India’s most sought-after IPO of 2025: Urban Co. set for market debut today
Urban Co. will begin trading in Mumbai on Wednesday after wrapping up India’s most oversubscribed major initial public offering this year, Bloomberg reported.
- September 17, 2025 09:34
Urban Company share price listing live today: GMP signals nearly 60% premium listing
Shares of the tech startup, popular for providing services from plumbing and house cleaning to masseurs, are trading at a premium of at least 60% over 103 rupees ($1.17), the top end of its IPO range, according to Investorgain.com and IPOcentral.in, which track informal price activity in the unregulated market.
Bloomberg report
Published on September 17, 2025

Title   : India’s most sought-after IPO of 2025: Urban Co. set for market debut today
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-17T03:10:39
Fetched : 2025-09-17T04:21:48.488660
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/indias-most-sought-after-ipo-of-2025-urban-co-set-for-market-debut-today/article70059609.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Urban Co. will begin trading in Mumbai on Wednesday after wrapping up India’s most oversubscribed major initial public offering this year.
The rent-a-service firm could be poised for a strong start as its shares on the gray market were trading more than 60% above the high end of the price marketed during the IPO.
IPO bids exceed 100 times on offer
Investors flocked to the stock during the $215 million IPO, bidding more than 100 times the number of shares on sale, making it the most sought-after new listing of 2025 in India among deals of $100 million or above, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.
Urban’s IPO has raised optimism its success will rub off on other Indian startups. A slew of companies — from eyewear retailer Lenskart Solutions Ltd. to e-commerce retailer Meesho Ltd. and Walmart Inc.-backed PhonePe are preparing to list their shares.
Urban’s offering saw strong participation from both institutional and retail investors. The deal included the sale of new and existing shares.
On-demand services fuel Urban’s growth story
Thanks to India’s abundance of cheap labour, Urban allows users to book many types of service professionals — from hair dressers to fumigators and plumbers — at competitive prices and fast. Its most used service is hiring people in beauty — including waxing, manicures and haircuts — followed by cleaning, according to a preliminary prospectus.
Investor demand for the firm’s shares reflect growing interest for companies benefiting from the country’s millions strong middle-class that seeks on-demand services. Urban is also seen benefiting from India’s move to cut taxes on everyday items as the South Asian nation looks to cushion the economy from US President Donald Trump’s 50% tariffs.
The estimated total addressable market for Urban’s home services stood at $59 billion last year and is projected to almost double by 2029, according to Urban’s IPO document.
More stories like this are available on bloomberg.com
Published on September 17, 2025

