Title   : Consumer product companies gearing up for new GST regime with reduced prices on smaller packs, pre-booking offers 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-16T15:07:45
Fetched : 2025-09-17T04:38:59.293676
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/consumer-product-companies-gearing-up-for-new-gst-regime-with-reduced-prices-on-smaller-packs-pre-booking-offers/article70057777.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
As consumer product companies gear up to transition to new GST rates, players such as Parle Products and Mother Dairy are reducing prices not just on bigger packs but also on smaller packs priced at popular points such as ₹5 and ₹10. At the same time, some AC and LED TV makers and dealers have started giving attractive pre-booking offers with reduced pricing in line with revised GST rates to consumers in the run-up to September 22.
Mayank Shah, Vice-President, Parle Products told businessline, “We have begun gearing up for price reduction in line with the new GST rates. FMCG companies have inventory of wrappers used for packaging with printed labels for 2-3 months and we cannot discard it. So new MRPs will be displayed through ink jet printing along with old MRPs on the packs. This reduction of price will be done on both bigger and smaller packs such as those priced at ₹5 and ₹10, as we want to ensure benefits are passed to consumers. Over a period of time, we will restore the popular price points such as ₹5 and ₹10 with higher grammage packs.”
Challenges faced
Last week, several industry players had stated that there are challenges in immediately passing on GST benefits on smaller packs citing coinage issues at the retail end.
Manish Bandlish, Managing Director, Mother Dairy, said, “We are passing 100 per cent of the tax benefit to our consumers effective September 22. With the GST reduction, our entire portfolio now falls either under the exempted or nil or the lowest slab of 5 per cent. In ice creams, for instance, we recognise that the ₹ 10 — our lowest unit pack – serves as the entry point for many consumers. By revising it to ₹ 9, we are ensuring the benefit of the tax reduction is passed on equitably. With UPI becoming the preferred mode of payment, we do not anticipate any significant discomfort related to coinage.”
Pre-booking offers
In a bid to liquidate older inventory, ahead of the GST implementation date, some consumer durables players have started giving attractive pre-booking offers for air-conditioners and LED TVs.
Haier India has rolled out pre-booking offers on air-conditioners with added benefits for September 10-21 period. Avneet Singh Marwah, CEO, Super Plastronics Pvt Ltd, said, “We are introducing pre-booking offers on LED TVs across our licensee brands of Thomson, Kodak and Blaupunkt, with reduced pricing in line with GST reforms, which will be billed and delivered from September 22 onwards.”
Another industry senior executive added that several dealers are giving pre-booking offers on air-conditioners to be able to sell older inventory after a wash out summer season but also to manage higher demand anticipated with the start of Navratris
Published on September 16, 2025

