Net Profit (TTM/latest) (2025-09-17): 19.58B INR

Title   : Redington shares surge 5%, up nearly 25% in just 2 sessions. What’s fuelling the rally? 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-17T05:04:21
Fetched : 2025-09-17T05:18:45.085676
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/redington-shares-surge-5-up-nearly-25-in-just-2-sessions-whats-fuelling-the-rally/articleshow/123935776.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The counter is seeing renewed interest as it handles the supply chain for IT and mobility products, including Apple’s iPhone. The company has a long-standing partnership with Apple, dating back to a 2007 distribution agreement for Apple products in India. Redington manages logistics, warehousing, and distribution to resellers and retailers across India, the Middle East, Turkey, Africa, and South Asia.
Also read: GST2.0 effect: M&M, Hyundai, TVS & Ashok Leyland best placed this festive season, says Nomura
The company posted a 12% growth in net profits of Rs 275 crore in the first quarter of FY26, compared to Rs 246 crore in the same period a year ago. The company’s revenue for the June quarter stood at Rs 25,952 crore, a 22% increase year-on-year from Rs 21,282 crore. Though the company’s net profit and revenue grew on a year-on-year basis, this was significantly lower on a sequential basis.
The company said that its performance was supported by solid execution across businesses and geographies and securing new opportunities in technology & cloud Solutions. From a business perspective, strong momentum was a result of high growth in the premium mobility segment and large deal wins & execution in India & UAE.
From a technical perspective, Redington Ltd.’s technical readings point to a near-term bearish bias with mixed longer-term signals: the MACD readings of about -0.7and -5.6 are below the zero line, which means the short-term moving average is beneath the longer-term moving average and momentum is tilted to the downside.
Read more: This smallcap stock jumps 40% in just 5 trading sessions. Should you book profits?
The 14-day RSI at 72 (on a 0–100 scale), is considered overbought. This implies that stock may show pullback.
At about 9:30 am, shares of the company were trading at Rs 293, higher by 1.2% from the last close on the NSE. Redington shares have risen 45% on a year-to-date basis.
